  subhead="You are mid-skim when the phone rings. They hang up after two rings. Five seconds later, they get a text from your plastering business: 'Sorry we missed your call — we are on a plastering job and will call you back within the hour.' They wait. The next plastering contractor never gets the call."
  scenario="It is 11:20am on a Monday. You are in a bathroom in Altrincham, skimming around a newly installed shower niche — the kind of fiddly work that takes concentration and clean hands. Your phone rings once in the hallway and stops. The caller — a homeowner three miles away who needs their dining room ceiling replaced after a leak — decides you must be too busy and starts scrolling Google for the next plasterer. Then their phone buzzes: 'Thanks for calling Maxwell Plastering. Sorry we missed your call — we are currently on a job. We will ring you back by lunchtime. If it is urgent, reply to this text and we will prioritise.' They put their phone down and wait. You call them at 12:45 and book the job. Without the text-back, they would have called someone else at 11:21."
